e-mail: promed@promedmail.org
[The bacterium that causes Pierce's Disease is _Xylella fastidiosa_.
According to Alexander Purcell, University of California (Berkeley), the
glassy-winged sharpshooter has become locally abundant in Riverside and San
Diego counties. Vineyards within a mile of citrus or avocado groves are at
greatest risk. Management of the disease includes reducing numbers of
glassy-winged sharpshooters and removal of diseased vines as soon as
possible after appearance of Pierce's Disease. - Mod.DH
